Joey and I will be reading children’s books for entertainment during these weird times for you and your children. I hope you enjoy it as much as we loved reading it. 💕 Sending love.
—————————————————
This book was one of my favorites growing up! I LOVE the illustrations and just everything about it. Did you read this book as a child too? 
Voiced by @joeyrudman and me! ☺️
Custom music by @philgood.audio

node.text:
Hi There! 👋🏼
There are a lot of new faces around here. Let me reintroduce myself and our little family! My name is Amanda, I am an artist living in Los Angeles. I happened to be in town by chance and stayed way longer than my intended two week visit. (It has been 8 years!) I fell in love with a beautiful, kind and funny guy who was living in the apartment building I just moved into 6 years ago. @joeyrudman and I are now married and have a beautiful son named Benny. Settling into our new roles as parents has been so much fun!
I have been illustrating our journey together for 5 years.
To those who have been a part of my journey for a while, thank you for your constant love, support and appreciation. 💕
To those who just got here- 
Nice to meet you and welcome!
I have a personal page where I document our lives through pictures and videos if you’d like to be friends on there too! @amanda.oleander

node.text:
Drawing 60/100 of the drawing a day for 100 days challenge. 
Two years ago Joey and I went snorkeling in Bora Bora, we swam with pretty big sharks in the wild and bonded over fish and coral we got to experience together. I wasn’t able to capture those moments in a way that felt right until today. We went with a small group of people but it felt like it was just the two of us and the ocean. When you have gear on you can’t exactly talk to each other but with just one look through the goggles we felt each other’s excitement. (Posting the shark video in my IG stories) 
———————————————
Have you snorkeled before? 
What’s your most exciting snorkeling experience and where did it take place?

node.text:
Drawing 59/100 of the drawing a day for 100 days challenge. 

This is inspired by last night’s sleep walking episode. @joeyrudman walked over to the dresser, picked up a shirt and told me he was looking for Benny’s “pitman”. I asked him what a pitman was and he started to describe Benny’s baby wrap carrier. I told him he was sleep walking and there’s no such thing as a pitman. Frustrated he couldn’t find the pitman and that I didn’t know what it was he picked up his phone to google it and show me but quickly
realized it didn’t exist in this world so he fell back asleep to look for it somewhere else. 
———————————————
Sleep walking stories? 
We want to hear them! Comment them below 💤

During my pregnancy I walked everyday in my neighborhood and took photographs of the beautiful flowers I’d pass along the way. 
I’m excited to share that those illustrations ended up on @lagottaofficial ‘s beautiful bathing suits. It’s an honor to collaborate with this sustainably thoughtful, woman owned brand. ( @valeriadelrey )
The first time I went to the beach during my pregnancy I was wearing a LaGotta piece and now the first time I am wearing a bathing suit postpartum it is a LaGotta I helped create! 
They have mommy and me matching bathing suits that are so unique and adorable, I can’t wait for Benny to fit into his matching shorts! I hope you enjoy these limited time designs and high quality buttery fabrics which are also UPF 50+. 💕
